The Director, Army Public Relations, Brig.-Gen. Onyema Nwachukwu disclosed this in a statement on Tuesday. The Nigerian Army (NA) has approved a list of hotlines to monitor and report any suspicious activity or acts of violence by unscrupulous persons or group of persons capable of disrupting the peaceful conduct of the 2023 general elections, as well as the conduct of troops deployed to provide security during the polls.  The Director, Army Public Relations, Brig.-Gen. Onyema Nwachukwu disclosed this in a statement on Tuesday.  According to the statement, the action is part of Nigerian Army’s move to support the lead security agency, the police for the successful conduct of free, fair and peaceful elections.  “It could be recalled that the NA had earlier produced and circulated Codes of Conduct and Rules of Engagement for Operation Safe Conduct to formations and Units to provide guidance and ensure that troops operate within the provisions of the codes and rules.  “Members of the general public are please enjoined to call the phone numbers below in their various states including the Federal Capital Territory Abuja to report any security breach during the elections,” the statement read.  The numbers are as follows: 1.   ABIA STATE 08031113129  2. ADAMAWA STATE 08022750987  3. AKWA-IBOM STATE 07034470916  4. ANAMBRA STATE 07035891185  5. BAUCHI STATE 08128063675  6. BAYELSA STATE 08033241005  7. BENUE STATE 08080754339  8. BORNO STATE 09099616160 08086987079  9. CROSS RIVER STATE 08037084192  10. DELTA STATE 07035070797  11. EBONYI STATE 08158274048  12. EDO STATE 09066325953  13. EKITI STATE 08037851448  14. ENUGU STATE 0903210221208023097458  15. GOMBE STATE 07063908779 08082557782  16. IMO STATE 07034907427  17. JIGAWA STATE 07017791414 08100144363  18. KADUNA STATE 07031544227 08028580978 08035242633  19. KANO STATE 08038432656  20. KASTINA STATE 08108854061 09012998054  21. KEBBI STATE 09130213661  22. KOGI STATE 08033217964  23. KWARA STATE 09060001270  24. LAG